-- Socar Plans to Build Four Offshore Drilling Rigs for $4 Billion
-- B y   Z u l f u g a r   A g a y e v
-- 2013-02-01T17:53:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-01/socar-plans-to-build-four-offshore-drilling-rigs-for-4-billion.html
State Oil Co. of Azerbaijan, also
known as Socar, plans to build four floating drilling rigs in
the next seven years at a total cost of $4 billion.  The rigs will have a capacity to drill for oil and natural
gas in the Caspian Sea at a depth of 1,000 meters (3,281 feet),
Socar President Rovnaq Abdullayev told reporters today in the
Azeri capital, Baku.  As many as 15,000 people will be involved in the
construction of the rigs, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zulfugar Agayev in Baku at 
 zagayev@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hellmuth Tromm at 
 htromm@bloomberg.net  